cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.LG. 

The paper presents a neural network approach for predicting missing entity type information in knowledge bases, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of short entity descriptions and related entity information as input suggests a natural language processing (cs.CL) component. The experimental evaluation is conducted using the DBpedia knowledge base, which is a database (cs.DB) of structured information extracted from Wikipedia. The task of assigning types to entities is also relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
